%matplotlib inline

sqlite
drop table if exists transaction_dat_enr; 
create table transaction_dat_enr as
select
    -- acct
    a.acct_id, 
    f.create_dt acct_create_dt, 
    f.payment_type acct_type, 
    -- txn
    a.create_dt txn_create_dt, 
    a.content_id txn_content_id, -- could be either app_id or iap_id 
    a.price txn_price, 
    a.device_id txn_device_id, 
    c.device_name txn_device_name, 
    a.txn_type, 
    -- app
    a.app_id, 
    b.app_name, 
    b.category_id app_category_id, 
    e.category_name app_category_name, 
    b.device_id app_device_id, 
    d.device_name app_device_name
from
    (
        -- iap
        select
            a.*, 
            b.parent_app_content_id app_id, 
            b.type txn_type
        from
            transaction_dat a
            join in_app_dat b on a.content_id=b.content_id
        union all
        -- app purchase or other cases
        select
            a.*, 
            b.content_id app_id, 
            null txn_type
        from
            transaction_dat a
            join app_dat b on a.content_id=b.content_id
    ) a
    left join app_dat b on a.app_id=b.content_id
    left join device_ref c on a.device_id=c.device_id
    left join device_ref d on b.device_id=d.device_id
    left join category_ref e on b.category_id=e.category_id
    left join account_dat f on a.acct_id=f.acct_id
;

transaction count for paid app¶

Even for these records that txn_prices equal to 0, these could from a paid app. So we need to get the paid apps first and then calculate the set difference to get the free apps.

tmp = data[['acct_id', 'txn_create_dt', 'app_name']].sort_values(['acct_id', 'txn_create_dt'], ascending=[True, True])
tmp2 = pd.concat([tmp, tmp.groupby('acct_id').shift(-1)], axis=1)
tmp2.columns = ['acct_id', 'txn_create_dt', 'app_name', 'nxt_txn_create_dt', 'nxt_app_name']
tmp2 = tmp2[~tmp2.nxt_app_name.isnull()]

tmp2['app_name~nxt_app_name'] = tmp2.app_name.str.cat(tmp2.nxt_app_name, sep=' ~ ')
tmp2['interval_days'] = (pd.to_datetime(tmp2.nxt_txn_create_dt) - pd.to_datetime(tmp2.txn_create_dt)).dt.days
In [56]:
tmp = pd.concat([tmp2.groupby('app_name~nxt_app_name').size(), tmp2.groupby('app_name~nxt_app_name')['interval_days'].mean(), tmp2.groupby('app_name~nxt_app_name')['interval_days'].std()], axis=1)
tmp.columns = ['cnt', 'interval_days_avg', 'interval_days_std']
tmp['cnt_pct'] = tmp.cnt / tmp.cnt.sum()
tmp = tmp.sort_values('cnt', ascending=False)
